\f0\b\fs50 \cf0 Blanched Crudites with Herb Dip
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\b \cf2 Serves: 
\b0 \cf0 4 to 6 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 pound asparagus\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 pound carrots, sliced diagonally in 1-inch chunks\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 pint {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/tomato/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cherry tomatoes}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 heads radicchio\
{\listtext	\'95	}Herb Dip, recipe follows\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Prepare a large pot of boiling salted water, and fill a large bowl with ice water.\
Remove the tough bottoms of the asparagus stalks. If they are thick, peel the stems half-way up the stalk.\
Add the carrots to the pot of boiling water and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/blanch/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 blanch}} for 1 minute. Immediately remove the carrots with a slotted spoon and plunge them in the bowl of ice water. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/drain/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Drain}} the carrots when fully cooled.\
Add the asparagus to the boiling water and blanch for 1 minute. Immediately remove the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/asparagus/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 asparagus}} with a slotted spoon and plunge them into the reserved bowl of ice water. Drain the asparagus when fully cooled.\
Slice the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/radicchio/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 radicchio}} into wedges.\
Arrange the carrots, asparagus, cherry tomatoes, and radicchio on a platter and serve with the Herb Dip.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs42 \cf0 Herb Dip:
\b0 \
8 ounces {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cream-cheese/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cream cheese}}, at room temperature\
1/2 cup {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sour-cream/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 sour cream}}\
1/2 cup mayonnaise\
4 scallions, white and green parts, minced\
2 tablespoons fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/parsley/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 parsley}} leaves, minced\
1 tablespoon fresh dill, minced\
1 teaspoon {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/salt/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 kosher salt}}\
3/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\
Place the cream cheese, sour cream, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mayonnaise/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mayonnaise}}, scallions, parsley, dill, salt, and pepper in the bowl of an electric {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mixer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mixer}} fitted with the paddle attachment and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/blend/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 blend}}. Serve at room temperature.\
Yield: 2 cups
